 "notes": [
  "A BLANK cell is not a zero. O-10 and O-9 have no published rate at low years of service, and W-5 none before 20 years, because nobody holds that grade that early. The site renders these as absent, never as $0.",
  "O-1E, O-2E and O-3E are the rates for an officer with at least four years of prior ENLISTED service. They pay materially more than the plain O-1/O-2/O-3 rate, and almost no pay chart a recruit is shown includes them \u2014 yet enlisting first and commissioning later is one of the most common routes this site's readers will actually take.",
  "Basic pay for the most senior grades is capped by law at Level II of the Executive Schedule. The table figure is the uncapped rate.",
  "This is BASIC PAY ONLY. It excludes BAH, BAS, and every special and incentive pay \u2014 which together are a large share of real compensation."
 ],
